id: pm-8fx3
title: Deduplicate front-matter key-order contract literals in tests
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: jscpd found tests/unit/shared-constants-errors.spec.ts copies the full FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER array from src/core/shared/constants.ts. Representative clone: constants.ts:46-115 vs shared-constants-errors.spec.ts:53-122. The literal copy catches accidental key-order changes, but it is large and easy to update mechanically without noticing intended contract changes. Existing pm-why9 covers default status/workflow model duplication, not this front-matter contract literal. Fix by replacing the long copied array with a smaller contract fixture strategy: either a named snapshot/golden file with clear update intent, or assertions over stable sentinel ordering and required membership that preserve contract value without a full in-test copy."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: code-quality,dedup,serialization,tests
created_at: "2026-05-22T19:09:00.475Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-22T19:09:25.448Z"
author: codex-dup-audit
acceptance_criteria: shared-constants tests no longer inline-copy the entire FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER array; the replacement still catches accidental front-matter ordering or missing required keys; serialization/release-readiness expectations remain deterministic; focused shared-constants tests and pnpm build pass.
parent: pm-rnpb
